#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.92"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.92:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: loṇaphalavaggo (bj, s1-3, km) | loṇaphalavagga (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.92:0.2"
msgid "10. Loṇakapallavagga "
msgstr "10. A Lump of Salt "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.92:0.3"
msgid "92. Accāyikasutta "
msgstr "92. Urgent "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.240, sc1
msgctxt "an3.92:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, kassakassa gahapatissa accāyikāni karaṇīyāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a farmer has three urgent duties. "

msgctxt "an3.92:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.92:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, kassako gahapati sīghaṃ sīghaṃ khettaṃ sukaṭṭhaṃ karoti sumatikataṃ. "
msgstr "A farmer swiftly makes sure the field is well ploughed and tilled. "

msgctxt "an3.92:1.4"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ khettaṃ sukaṭṭhaṃ karitvā sumatikataṃ sīghaṃ sīghaṃ bījāni patiṭṭhāpeti. "
msgstr "Next they swiftly plant seeds in season. "

msgctxt "an3.92:1.5"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ bījāni patiṭṭhāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ udakaṃ abhinetipi apanetipi. "
msgstr "When the time is right, they swiftly irrigate or drain the field. "

msgctxt "an3.92:1.6"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi kassakassa gahapatissa accāyikāni karaṇīyāni. "
msgstr "These are the three urgent duties of a farmer. "

msgctxt "an3.92:1.7"
msgid "Tassa kho taṃ, bhikkhave, kassakassa gahapatissa natthi sā iddhi vā ānubhāvo vā: "
msgstr "That farmer has no special power or ability to say: "

# NOTE: http://ricepedia.org/rice-as-a-plant/growth-phases
msgctxt "an3.92:1.8"
msgid "‘ajjeva me dhaññāni jāyantu, sveva gabbhīni hontu, uttarasveva paccantū’ti. "
msgstr "‘Let the crops germinate today! Let them flower tomorrow! Let them ripen the day after!’ "

msgctxt "an3.92:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, hoti so samayo yaṃ tassa kassakassa gahapatissa tāni dhaññāni utupariṇāmīni jāyantipi gabbhīnipi honti paccantipi. "
msgstr "But there comes a time when that farmer’s crops germinate, flower, and ripen as the seasons change. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.92:2.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tīṇimāni bhikkhussa accāyikāni karaṇīyāni. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant has three urgent duties. "

msgctxt "an3.92:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.92:2.3"
msgid "Adhisīlasikkhāsamādānaṃ, adhicittasikkhāsamādānaṃ, adhipaññāsikkhāsamādānaṃ—"
msgstr "Undertaking the training in the higher ethics, the higher mind, and the higher wisdom. "

msgctxt "an3.92:2.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi bhikkhussa accāyikāni karaṇīyāni. "
msgstr "These are the three urgent duties of a mendicant. "

msgctxt "an3.92:2.5"
msgid "Tassa kho taṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno natthi sā iddhi vā ānubhāvo vā: "
msgstr "That mendicant has no special power or ability to say: "

msgctxt "an3.92:2.6"
msgid "‘ajjeva me anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccatu sve vā uttarasve vā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Let my mind be freed from defilements by not grasping today! Or tomorrow! Or the day after!’ "

msgctxt "an3.92:2.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, hoti so samayo yaṃ tassa bhikkhuno adhisīlampi sikkhato adhicittampi sikkhato adhipaññampi sikkhato anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "But there comes a time—as that mendicant trains in the higher ethics, the higher mind, and the higher wisdom—that their mind is freed from defilements by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.92:3.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should train like this: "

msgctxt "an3.92:3.2"
msgid "‘tibbo no chando bhavissati adhisīlasikkhāsamādāne, tibbo chando bhavissati adhicittasikkhāsamādāne, tibbo chando bhavissati adhipaññāsikkhāsamādāne’ti. "
msgstr "‘We will have keen enthusiasm for undertaking the training in the higher ethics, the higher mind, and the higher wisdom.’ "

msgctxt "an3.92:3.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.92:3.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

